        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">α-fibre grain orientation is a type of grain orientation which is quality of polycrystal, i.e., several grains, oriented in the following way: &lt;110&gt; family of crystallographic directions are oriented parallel to the rolling direction (RD) of a sheet material.</skos:definition>
