        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Goss texture component</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel>{110}&lt;100&gt;</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Goss texture component is a type of grain orientation which is a quality of some polycrystal, i.e., several grains, oriented in the following way: &lt;100&gt; family of crystallographic directions are oriented parallel to the rolling direction (RD) of a sheet material and {110} family of crystallographic planes are oriented parallel to the rolling plane of a sheet material.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


